terminale 1
Navigate to your project folder with this syntax :
    cd /mnt/c/path/to/your/project
example:
    cd /mnt/c/Users/ste_1/PycharmProjects/fastApiProject

Create and Activate a Virtual Environment :
    source name_of_your_environment/bin/activate
example:
    source venv_wsl/bin/activate



Running the Worker and API
Start the Celery Worker: 
    python3 -m celery -A worker.celery_app worker --loglevel=info





Terminal 2 (The API)
Open a new WSL terminal window.
Navigate to the project folder with this syntax:
    cd /mnt/c/path/to/your/project
example:
    cd /mnt/c/Users/ste_1/PycharmProjects/fastApiProject


Activate the environment: 
    source name_of_your_environment/bin/activate
example:
    source venv_wsl/bin/activate



Start the FastAPI Server:
uvicorn main:app --reload


Testing the Setup
Open your Windows browser to http://127.0.0.1:8000/docs
